# Musubi project rules (Cursor)

This file is Cursor's always-apply rule pack. The full contract for every coding agent on this repo lives at [AGENTS.md](mdc:../../AGENTS.md) (non-Claude tools) and [CLAUDE.md](mdc:../../CLAUDE.md) (Claude Code). Cursor with Claude as its backing model should treat both as authoritative. Read:

- [AGENTS.md](mdc:../../AGENTS.md)
- [docs/AGENT-PROCESS.md](mdc:../../docs/AGENT-PROCESS.md) — multi-agent concurrency model
- [docs/Musubi/00-index/agent-guardrails.md](mdc:../../docs/Musubi/00-index/agent-guardrails.md) — authoritative rule expansion

## The four non-negotiables

1. **Stay inside `owns_paths`.** Your slice's `docs/Musubi/_slices/<slice-id>.md` names what you may write. Read anywhere, write only there.
2. **Canonical API is frozen per version.** Don't edit `src/musubi/api/`, `openapi.yaml`, `proto/` unless your slice is `slice-api-v*`.
3. **Tests first.** The spec's `## Test Contract` section is authoritative; first commit on your branch is the test file realising it.
4. **Don't silently rebase the spec.** Spec edits that accompany code go in the same PR, with `spec-update: <doc-path>` on the commit.

## Test Contract Closure Rule

Every bullet in the spec's `## Test Contract` at handoff is in one of three states:

1. **Passing test** with a function name matching the bullet text verbatim (`_` for spaces).
2. **Skipped** with `@pytest.mark.skip(reason="deferred to slice-<id>: <why>")`.
3. **Declared out-of-scope** in the slice's `## Work log`, with a named follow-up home.

Silent omission is a request-changes. Cursor's "fix all" / "apply to all files" tendencies should not quietly drop bullets — pass each through review.

## Method-ownership rule

If the method's code lives in your `owns_paths`, you own it. Don't defer methods to slices that merely expose them.

## Dual-update rule (vault ↔ GitHub Issue)

Claim / handoff / block each touch both sides **in the same PR**:

| Transition | Issue command | Frontmatter change |
|---|---|---|
| Claim | `gh issue edit <n> --add-assignee @me --add-label status:in-progress --remove-label status:ready` | `status: ready → in-progress`, `owner: <your-agent-id>` |
| Handoff | `gh issue edit <n> --add-label status:in-review --remove-label status:in-progress` | `status: in-progress → in-review` |
| Block | `gh issue edit <n> --add-label status:blocked` + comment | `status: <prev> → blocked`, work-log entry |
| Done | PR body `Closes #<n>` (auto-close) | `status: in-review → done` |

`make issue-check` detects drift. Merge-blocker at review.

## Hard prohibitions (automatic revert)

- `except Exception: pass`
- `os.environ` reads outside `src/musubi/config.py`
- `time.sleep()` in production code paths
- Hardcoded hosts / ports / collection names / thresholds — use placeholders for topology (see `.agent-context.local.md`)
- New top-level dependencies without an ADR
- `git push --force` on shared branches
- `--no-verify` on commits
- Committing `.agent-context.local.md`, `.env.local`, `.secrets/`, `*.pem`, `*.key`, `id_*`

## Style

- Python 3.12 + strict mypy + ruff format + ruff check + pydantic v2
- `Result[T, E]` at module boundaries
- Async public surface
- Structured JSON logs, correlation IDs propagate, no f-strings in log messages
- **No `print()`**

## File patterns

- `src/musubi/<module>/` → implementation
- `tests/<module>/` mirrors it
- `docs/Musubi/<NN-section>/<doc>.md` → specs
- `docs/Musubi/_slices/slice-<id>.md` → your work order
- `docs/Musubi/13-decisions/NNNN-<slug>.md` → ADRs

## Cursor-specific guidance

- **Be skeptical of "apply all suggested edits" across files.** That feature loves to sweep into `forbidden_paths`. Hold the slice's allowed paths in mind; reject cross-slice edits.
- **Cursor auto-apply can edit `src/musubi/types/` when it "helps" unify types.** Don't let it. Only `slice-types` agents modify that directory.
- **Before committing, run `make check && make agent-check` locally** — catches drift before GitHub CI does.

## Agent identification

Cursor working with a Claude backing model: identify as `cursor-claude` in slice work logs. With Gemini: `cursor-gemini`. With GPT: `cursor-gpt`.
